column7: To reduce the extent of farm-related youth injuries , the National Institute of Occupational Safety and Health ( NIOSH ) and the Marshfield Clinic Research Foundation have issued a set of guidelines known as the North American Guidelines for Children's Agricultural Tasks ( NAGCAT ) based on child development principles that matched children 's abilities with the requirements of specific farm work .
